text:
King's Highway, between East 21st Street and Nøstrand Ave., showing B.G. Hitching's house at the left, and the "Senate" of "The Club House" in the center of the view.
April 1923.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
title: Brooklyn: Kings Highway - 21st Street (East)

text:
(1) King's Highway, east from King's Highway and Ave. P., showing at left the B.G. Hitching's house and beyond it in the distance the "Senate" or "The Club House", both of which were demolished in 1928.

August 1924.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

(2) The same, showing the N.W. corner of East 26th Street and King's Highway, the home of Pat Whallen in 1873. This house still stands, and is No. 2519 King's Highway. In the background is the steel structure which, when completed, will be Congress Arms a 6-story apartment house.

August 1924.

Eugene L. Armbruster collection.
title: Brooklyn: Kings Highway - Avenue P
